da0b25c5182dcb925f913f3d1e32a17c::2025-1.summary: Severe floods caused by torrential rain and Cyclone Ditwah have affected Sri Lanka, Indonesia’s Sumatra, southern Thailand, and northern Malaysia, killing nearly 1,000 people in less than a week. Hundreds remain missing, especially in Indonesia and Sri Lanka, where rescue efforts are ongoing. Military and emergency teams have been deployed, but some areas remain inaccessible. This is Sri Lanka’s worst natural disaster since the 2004 tsunami.

ea16c6b4eec75f0785a5e09bcfba61aa::2025-1.summary: A long-lost painting by 17th-century Flemish artist Peter Paul Rubens, depicting the crucifixion of Jesus Christ, was discovered by an auctioneer in a Paris townhouse in 2024.
